overview: The user wanted to elevate the aesthetic appeal of their sleep
  questionnaire app, moving it from a generic look to a more professional and
  calming experience. I began by analyzing the existing design, identifying
  areas for improvement in color, layout, and component styling. I then
  implemented a new sleep-themed color palette, redesigned the main
  questionnaire form with subtle background elements and an enhanced progress
  indicator, and overhauled the welcome screen with feature cards. Crucially, I
  ensured consistency by updating all form field components and applying the new
  card-style grouping to all 14 sections of the questionnaire, replacing
  previous plain gray boxes. The report section also received a visual upgrade
  with consistent gradient headers. The outcome is a significantly more
  polished, cohesive, and user-friendly interface that aligns with the app's
  purpose of sleep health assessment.
